about.description: With help of DI you can use different parts of you system independently and combine their behavior really easy.

name: dependencies
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "dependencies" %}
{% set version = "1.0.0" %}
{% set file_ext = "tar.gz" %}
{% set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{% set hash_value = "b8dbd7560ac0de0f83ecca19c330235993edc1de63b1745841000a39b60f7ff6" %}

package:
  name: '{{ name|lower }}'
  version: '{{ version }}'

source:
  fn: '{{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ file_ext }}'
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ file_ext }}
  '{{ hash_type }}': '{{ hash_value }}'

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps"

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - poetry
    - python
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - dependencies
    - dependencies.contrib

about:
  home: https://github.com/dry-python/dependencies
  license: BSD 2-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: 'LICENSE'
  summary: Dependency Injection for Humans
  description: "With help of DI you can use different parts of you system independently and combine their behavior really easy."
  doc_url: 'http://dependencies.readthedocs.io/en/latest/'
  dev_url: 'https://github.com/dry-python/dependencies'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - nicoddemus
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.15
